Three armed men who robbed a man of his bag in Fordsburg,
Johannesburg, opened fire on police before driving off in a white BMW. The incident happened on Wednesday, said police spokesperson
Captain Mavela Masondo. Video footage of the incident circulated on social media. It is alleged that the victim was accosted by three armed
men after leaving the bank. They demanded the bag he was carrying. When the
victim ran to a nearby store, he was followed and robbed at gunpoint. Masondo said the robbers opened fire on police officers who
attended to the robbery. No officer was injured, Masondo said.  SOURCE: NEWS24